The author shares her unconventional journey to the White House as a result of a chance encounter with a stranger. While waitressing at a bakery, a woman asked her if she liked politics and gave her a business card. The woman turned out to be the president of a policy think tank in Illinois. After an internship at the think tank, the author received an email from the same woman about the White House Internship Program. Despite doubting her chances, she applied and was accepted. The author emphasizes the importance of seizing opportunities, even if they seem unlikely, as they can lead to unexpected paths. The article concludes with the announcement that the Summer 2018 White House Internship Program application is open.